00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:06,152
- My back feels like it might snap in two.
- That's right.

242
00:08:06,219 --> 00:08:07,587
But you have to look at ease.

243
00:08:07,721 --> 00:08:10,190
That's right.
But you have to look at ease.

244
00:08:10,457 --> 00:08:12,425
- Cross your legs, too.
- I did.

245
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,160
- This is...
- This is really uncomfortable for me.

246
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:16,029
I think I have cramps.

247
00:08:16,096 --> 00:08:17,931
- Did you do it? Then after that...
- I did it.

248
00:08:17,998 --> 00:08:19,799
Let's say Ha-jun is
the man you're trying to seduce.

249
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:21,267
You should look at him,

250
00:08:21,534 --> 00:08:25,472
but first, angle your head down like this
and then look up.

251
00:08:25,538 --> 00:08:26,473
So pretty.

252
00:08:26,539 --> 00:08:28,575
...and then look up.

253
00:08:28,641 --> 00:08:29,642
So pretty.

254
00:08:29,709 --> 00:08:31,611
- Game over.
- Do you understand?

255
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:32,579
- Okay.
- You try.

256
00:08:32,645 --> 00:08:34,280
- You try, Sun-ja.
- Here I go.

257
00:08:35,749 --> 00:08:37,517
You have to twist even more.

258
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:41,521
- Oh, that's it!
- Right.

259
00:08:41,588 --> 00:08:43,656
You're doing great.

260
00:08:44,224 --> 00:08:46,226
Think, "Let's see you try to resist me."

261
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,029
Hold on. Are you sure this worked?

262
00:08:49,095 --> 00:08:50,797
Did it work?

263
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:52,098
- Are you sure if it did?
- It almost worked.

264
00:08:52,165 --> 00:08:53,233
Oh, "almost"?

265
00:08:55,668 --> 00:08:57,370
I'm glad I have something to watch now.

266
00:08:57,437 --> 00:08:58,471
I'll definitely watch this.

267
00:08:58,538 --> 00:08:59,539
Are you done with filming?

268
00:08:59,606 --> 00:09:01,341
- Yes.
- It just wrapped up.

269
00:09:01,808 --> 00:09:02,742
- A few days ago.
- Not long ago.

270
00:09:02,809 --> 00:09:04,077
Are you going on a trip, then?

271
00:09:04,144 --> 00:09:05,478
- Since it's over?
- A trip?

272
00:09:05,645 --> 00:09:07,914
Yes, if I have time
after the promotions are done.

273
00:09:07,981 --> 00:09:09,049
Where are we going?

274
00:09:09,783 --> 00:09:10,917
Where are...

275
00:09:12,018 --> 00:09:13,053
Where are we going?

276
00:09:13,186 --> 00:09:14,287
Where did we go last time?

277
00:09:14,354 --> 00:09:15,722
Last time,

278
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:18,792
we went to Paris first, and then to Spain.

279
00:09:18,925 --> 00:09:20,427
- Right.
- So where to this time?

280
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:24,497
- You can pick the place, Ha-jun.
- Me?

281
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:26,299
- Italy?
- Italy it is.

282
00:09:26,766 --> 00:09:28,234
North or south?

283
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:29,602
I want to go south.

284
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:30,904
Okay, got it.

285
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:32,539
Don't follow us there, Min-young.

286
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:34,441
- Where are you going again?
- The south of Italy.

287
00:09:34,507 --> 00:09:39,245
Well, someone's waiting for me in Sicily,
so I'll be in the area too.

288
00:09:39,312 --> 00:09:40,647
- Who's waiting for you in Sicily?
- For real?

289
00:09:40,713 --> 00:09:41,614
Just someone I know.

290
00:09:41,681 --> 00:09:43,516
- She talks big, too.
- Really?

291
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:45,685
- She's bluffing.
- She's lying.

292
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:46,753
- I'm telling the truth.
- You're the bigger liar.

293
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:48,288
No, she's a liar.

294
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:49,989
Are we supposed to believe she has someone

295
00:09:50,056 --> 00:09:51,891
- waiting for her in Sicily?
- It could be true.

296
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:54,394
I haven't been there yet,
but I probably have a friend there.

297
00:09:54,461 --> 00:09:56,096
She's lying. I'm sure of it.

298
00:09:56,729 --> 00:09:58,998
She's lying!

299
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:01,868
Was this your first time
doing a TV show together?

300
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,236
- Yes.
- So...

301
00:10:03,503 --> 00:10:04,504
It's the first time we met.

302
00:10:04,571 --> 00:10:06,039
- Oh, really?
- Yes, first time ever.

303
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:06,973
- First time ever?
- Yes.

304
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,875
I've met her from time to time.

305
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:10,443
You remember, right?

306
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:12,445
- You mean in our club?
- The Cops and Robbers club?

307
00:10:12,512 --> 00:10:13,546
- No, not the club.
- Then...

308
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,914
Where else did you meet her?

309
00:10:14,981 --> 00:10:16,683
- It's...
- Come on. Tell us where.

310
00:10:17,851 --> 00:10:19,152
She was on the radio show.

311
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:20,787
- Oh, that show?
- She could've been on any radio show.

312
00:10:20,854 --> 00:10:22,422
- You remember, right?
- It's not a big deal.

313
00:10:22,489 --> 00:10:23,790
- Not a big deal at all.
- You remember!

314
00:10:23,857 --> 00:10:25,191
- I do.
- You remember!

315
00:10:25,258 --> 00:10:28,862
Yours is the only radio show
I've ever been on.

316
00:10:29,028 --> 00:10:31,231
- So you know what I told her?
- She was on your radio show.

317
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:33,166
You know what I told her then?

318
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:35,068
I found her really funny,

319
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,103
so I told her
she should host a radio show herself.

320
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:38,771
- Really?
- I thought she'd be good at it.

321
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:40,406
- Do you remember?
- It was so long ago.

322
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,408
- Maybe ten years ago?
- And you know what she said?

323
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:45,378
She said, "I can't,
because I talk a lot of nonsense."

324
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:47,247
- I see.
- I see she hasn't changed at all.

325
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,315
- She still does.
- She's still talking nonsense.

326
00:10:49,382 --> 00:10:50,416
- She hasn't changed?
- She hasn't.

327
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:52,852
- Someone waiting for you in Sicily?
- She said there is someone.

328
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:55,021
- She's still at it.
- All the way in Italy.

329
00:10:55,088 --> 00:10:57,223
I think you and I
share a similar sense of humor.

330
00:10:58,024 --> 00:11:00,627
What were your first impressions
of each other

331
00:11:00,693 --> 00:11:01,928
when you met for this show?

332
00:11:02,195 --> 00:11:03,530
You said you'd never
met her before, right?

333
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:07,233
It felt like her character was
right there in the room with me.

334
00:11:07,634 --> 00:11:09,002
Her character from the script, I mean.

335
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:10,870
Was it on the day of
the first read-through?

336
00:11:10,937 --> 00:11:12,539
No, it was the day before that
with the director.

337
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:14,607
- When you all met with the director?
- Yes.

338
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:19,045
What was your first impression of Ha-jun?

339
00:11:19,245 --> 00:11:20,847
He looks kind of cold
and standoffish, right?

340
00:11:20,914 --> 00:11:22,482
Like a carnivorous dinosaur.

341
00:11:22,549 --> 00:11:23,716
- I see it.
- Yes, a dinosaur.

342
00:11:23,783 --> 00:11:25,485
I prefer people who look like that.

343
00:11:25,552 --> 00:11:27,387
So when he walked in

344
00:11:27,687 --> 00:11:30,657
with his eyes looking so cold and distant,

345
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:35,461
my immediate thought was,
"We're really going to hit it off."

346
00:11:35,528 --> 00:11:36,429
Same here.

347
00:11:36,496 --> 00:11:37,864
You could tell the show
would be a big hit?

348
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:40,166
I thought we'd look good together
and have great chemistry.

349
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:41,834
- I'm looking forward to it so much.
- I agree.

350
00:11:41,901 --> 00:11:45,205
The Min-young I know
has a knack for choosing great projects.

351
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:47,574
- Then this <i>Siren's Kiss</i>...
<i>- Siren's Kiss.</i>

352
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,642
How high do you think
the viewership rating will go?

353
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:53,146
Among ourselves,

354
00:11:53,213 --> 00:11:56,716
we decided to go on a vacation together
if it reaches 7%.

355
00:11:56,783 --> 00:11:58,084
Oh, 7%?

356
00:11:58,151 --> 00:11:59,452
What about you, Ha-jun?

357
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:02,322
- I had the same prediction.
- Around 7%?

358
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:05,458
And we also want it
to generate the most buzz.

359
00:12:05,525 --> 00:12:07,460
- That's a good strategy too.
- It will be.

360
00:12:07,527 --> 00:12:09,128
- That's a better metric of success
- Right.

361
00:12:09,195 --> 00:12:10,296
- than viewership ratings.
- That's more important.

362
00:12:10,363 --> 00:12:11,664
- The buzz it generates.
- Right.

363
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:12,665
- It's important.
- I have an idea.

364
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:15,268
Promise to do something
if the rating reaches 7%.

365
00:12:18,438 --> 00:12:20,139
Ha-jun is a great dancer.

366
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:24,110
He's the prince of Wando
and of dance, right?

367
00:12:24,177 --> 00:12:26,646
- The dancing king of Wando!
- Wando's best dancer.

368
00:12:26,713 --> 00:12:28,448
- Isn't that right?
- My goodness.

369
00:12:28,514 --> 00:12:29,482
This is great.

370
00:12:29,549 --> 00:12:31,351
- Let's go!
- Show us.

371
00:12:31,484 --> 00:12:33,886
- Let's go, Ha-jun!
- Let's go!

372
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:36,389
Let's see you shake it!

373
00:12:36,623 --> 00:12:37,957
You're good. Show them.

374
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:39,692
I'm not a dancer.

375
00:12:43,496 --> 00:12:45,531
I got thrown out of my seat.

376
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:50,436
Hey, did you forget
what I taught you already?

377
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:53,906
You have to twist your body more.

378
00:12:53,973 --> 00:12:55,341
- Right.
- I forgot.

379
00:12:55,408 --> 00:12:56,809
- Then what should we do?
- Just now,

380
00:12:56,876 --> 00:12:59,045
the way Sun-ja moved

381
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:00,346
- Too brazen?
- was too direct.

382
00:13:00,413 --> 00:13:02,048
- She was too eager.
- Then how should I do it?

383
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:03,650
- Min-young is a great dancer.
- What's the right way?

384
00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:04,550
- Show us.
- Show us.

385
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,786
Let's say you want to do this move.

386
00:13:06,853 --> 00:13:09,589
- Right.
- Then you have to twist like this.

387
00:13:09,822 --> 00:13:11,624
This is too boring.

388
00:13:11,691 --> 00:13:13,660
- It looks like you're on the toilet.
- Exactly, Sun-ja.

389
00:13:13,726 --> 00:13:15,495
- It looked weird.
- That was so sexy.

390
00:13:15,561 --> 00:13:17,163
Even just twisting a little bit

391
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:18,765
- makes all the difference.
- Twist it like this?

392
00:13:18,831 --> 00:13:19,699
- Goodness.
- Right?

393
00:13:19,766 --> 00:13:20,767
- Let's go.
- All right.

394
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:22,368
- One, two, three, four.
- Let's go.

395
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:24,637
Like this?

396
00:13:37,717 --> 00:13:38,918
My goodness.

397
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,788
That wasn't so bad, right?

398
00:13:42,188 --> 00:13:43,823
That was great.

399
00:13:43,890 --> 00:13:45,258
You were great.

400
00:13:45,325 --> 00:13:47,994
I'm so sorry,
but all that rapping made me dizzy.

401
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:49,529
That was amazing.

402
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:51,831
<i>After all that chaos,</i>
<i>there's only one thing you need.</i>

403
00:13:51,898 --> 00:13:55,468
<i>It's a glass of refreshing beer</i>
<i>paired with some fried chicken.</i>

404
00:13:55,535 --> 00:13:56,936
- My goodness.
- Do you want some beer?

405
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:58,671
- Sure.
- Yes.

406
00:13:58,738 --> 00:14:00,239
- You really want a glass?
- Sure.

407
00:14:00,306 --> 00:14:01,441
- Really?
- But I tend to

408
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,509
talk nonsense when I drink beer.

409
00:14:03,576 --> 00:14:04,477
That's good.

410
00:14:04,544 --> 00:14:06,879
You must've had some beer
before coming here, then.

411
00:14:07,046 --> 00:14:09,148
- You must've had a whole bucketful.
- If you get drunk,

412
00:14:09,215 --> 00:14:10,450
the ratings of this show will reach 7%.

413
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:12,618
- Exactly, Sun-i.
- We'll reach 7% ratings.

414
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:14,587
If we get her drunk,
we'll definitely reach 7%.

415
00:14:14,654 --> 00:14:15,722
- Of course.
- Then, and only then.

416
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:17,523
- Have some beer.
- This will generate some buzz.

417
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:20,093
You used to run
a tea house or something, didn't you?

418
00:14:20,426 --> 00:14:22,061
- That was a different place.
- Oh, really?

419
00:14:22,128 --> 00:14:23,062
- Exactly.
- I see.

420
00:14:23,129 --> 00:14:25,231
But I'll make sure to learn that dance.
It was so good.

421
00:14:25,431 --> 00:14:26,733
It was nothing.

422
00:14:26,966 --> 00:14:29,001
Let's get our ratings up to 7%.

423
00:14:29,969 --> 00:14:30,937
Right.

424
00:14:33,239 --> 00:14:35,808
It was nothing.
I'm not that good of a dancer,

425
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,177
- but it's just something I noticed.
- No, you're good.

426
00:14:39,045 --> 00:14:40,046
Here you go.

427
00:14:42,482 --> 00:14:44,417
Okay. Here you go.

428
00:14:44,951 --> 00:14:46,152
This is just drool.

429
00:14:46,219 --> 00:14:48,221
- Drool?
- Yes, it's drool.

430
00:14:48,287 --> 00:14:49,355
I beatboxed too hard.

431
00:14:49,422 --> 00:14:51,357
- Under her nose too.
- Hang on.

432
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,962
- And the side of her head.
- Where? Here?

433
00:14:56,028 --> 00:14:57,663
- No, not that side.
- Hold on.

434
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:00,166
- I see.
- This is so heartwarming.

435
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:02,368
This is some great
mise-en-scène right here.

436
00:15:02,435 --> 00:15:03,269
All done.

437
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:05,538
How was that?

438
00:15:05,605 --> 00:15:07,440
- Very nice.
- Was it okay?

439
00:15:07,507 --> 00:15:09,342
- That was very good.
- I've learned something new.

440
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:11,144
Here, have some freshly fried chicken.

441
00:15:11,644 --> 00:15:13,946
- It just got done.
- That looks delicious.

442
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:15,748
It's still steaming hot.

443
00:15:15,815 --> 00:15:17,183
- It's hot.
- Nice.

444
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,152
Hot and freshly fried.

445
00:15:20,153 --> 00:15:21,287
- Take one each.
- Is this real beer?

446
00:15:21,354 --> 00:15:23,322
Yes, it's real beer
from the keg right here.

447
00:15:23,389 --> 00:15:24,357
- It's real.
- Yes.

448
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:26,359
- Draft beer?
- Yes, draft beer.

449
00:15:26,859 --> 00:15:28,561
Do you usually drink a lot?

450
00:15:29,028 --> 00:15:31,931
I used to drink quite often,
but I didn't for eight months.

451
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:34,267
- You quit drinking?
- For the role, you know.

452
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,501
- That's so admirable.
- Right.

453
00:15:35,568 --> 00:15:37,537
So my tolerance might have gotten lower.

454
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:40,740
- You get drunk easily?
- It would've been nothing to the old me.

455
00:15:40,807 --> 00:15:41,941
Is it real beer?

456
00:15:44,811 --> 00:15:45,812
You know what?

457
00:15:47,313 --> 00:15:49,215
- Doesn't it taste great?
- Yes.

458
00:15:49,816 --> 00:15:51,984
You even twist your body
when you're drinking?

459
00:15:52,051 --> 00:15:53,453
- My goodness.
- Who drinks like that?

460
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:55,621
- It's ingrained in you!
- What is?

461
00:15:55,688 --> 00:15:57,323
- It's ingrained in you to be seductive.
- It's ingrained.

462
00:15:57,390 --> 00:15:58,257
Why?

463
00:15:58,324 --> 00:15:59,459
- You drank like this.
- Even while drinking.

464
00:15:59,525 --> 00:16:00,993
Who drinks beer like this?

465
00:16:01,060 --> 00:16:02,562
- That was incredible.
- Unbelievable.

466
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,063
I should start drinking like this too.

467
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:05,398
It was just manners.

468
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:07,033
- I'm never facing forward from now on.
- Right.

469
00:16:08,835 --> 00:16:09,969
What about it?

470
00:16:10,369 --> 00:16:14,140
Isn't anyone else from our club
joining us today?

471
00:16:14,207 --> 00:16:16,709
Well, it's not
one of our regular meetings.

472
00:16:16,776 --> 00:16:18,778
You two said
you had something to tell us, right?

473
00:16:18,845 --> 00:16:19,846
- That's why.
- Right.

474
00:16:19,912 --> 00:16:21,614
- Well--
- You asked to meet, Min-young.

475
00:16:21,681 --> 00:16:23,149
I have something to tell you too.

476
00:16:23,216 --> 00:16:24,317
- What?
- What?

477
00:16:24,584 --> 00:16:26,419
- You're making us nervous.
- What is it?

478
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:27,987
The club's president is joining us later.

479
00:16:28,054 --> 00:16:29,322
The president? Why?

480
00:16:29,388 --> 00:16:30,323
The president said he'd come.

481
00:16:30,389 --> 00:16:31,624
- What do you need to tell us?
- Why is he coming?

482
00:16:31,691 --> 00:16:32,825
What could it be?

483
00:16:32,892 --> 00:16:35,228
Then let's talk about that
when the president gets here.

484
00:16:35,294 --> 00:16:38,197
All right, then.
Let's eat and enjoy ourselves for now.

485
00:16:38,264 --> 00:16:40,299
