00:26:03,262 --> 00:26:04,763
On the other hand,
they're in the same weight class.

743
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:06,331
- What?
- Then it's like...

744
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:08,634
- In fact, she's in a higher class.
- Weight class...

745
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:10,269
- Weight class? Wait.
- Actually,

746
00:26:10,335 --> 00:26:11,904
she's two weight classes above him.

747
00:26:12,838 --> 00:26:14,773
- In that case...
- Then it was self-defense.

748
00:26:14,873 --> 00:26:16,742
- How much do you weigh?
- Then it was self-defense.

749
00:26:17,042 --> 00:26:18,744
- I weigh 66kg.
- I'm 80kg.

750
00:26:19,678 --> 00:26:21,647
- Then who...
- Wait a minute.

751
00:26:21,713 --> 00:26:24,183
- He actually does weigh less than I do.
- Hang on.

752
00:26:24,783 --> 00:26:26,752
- You're three classes above me.
- In terms of weight class?

753
00:26:27,086 --> 00:26:28,587
- Oh, for real?
- I checked.

754
00:26:28,654 --> 00:26:30,255
Did you move up a weight class?

755
00:26:30,355 --> 00:26:32,157
I had no chance at all from the start.

756
00:26:32,658 --> 00:26:34,626
As a student of mixed martial arts myself,

757
00:26:34,693 --> 00:26:36,395
this was an impossible fight
from the beginning.

758
00:26:36,462 --> 00:26:39,765
The one in the higher weight class
bit down first.

759
00:26:40,165 --> 00:26:41,066
This is unfair.

760
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:43,168
- Then you're completely at fault here.
- Wait.

761
00:26:43,235 --> 00:26:44,403
- Come on.
- That's right.

762
00:26:45,037 --> 00:26:46,205
This is ridiculous.

763
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:47,940
- That was on you.
- This isn't fair.

764
00:26:48,006 --> 00:26:49,374
Don't blame her too much, though.

765
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:51,210
- I couldn't see because it was night.
- Exactly.

766
00:26:51,276 --> 00:26:54,213
Besides, when Ha-jun and I
were scuffling before,

767
00:26:54,279 --> 00:26:55,647
he didn't hold back either.

768
00:26:55,714 --> 00:26:57,449
He went for an armbar.

769
00:26:57,516 --> 00:26:58,817
- No.
- That was too much.

770
00:26:58,884 --> 00:27:01,220
- I didn't.
- How could you do that to a woman?

771
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:02,621
Did you really do that?

772
00:27:02,888 --> 00:27:04,389
It wasn't an armbar,

773
00:27:04,456 --> 00:27:06,358
but a rear naked choke.

774
00:27:06,425 --> 00:27:07,626
- A rear naked choke?
- A rear naked choke?

775
00:27:07,726 --> 00:27:09,728
- Isn't that even worse?
- A rear naked choke?

776
00:27:09,795 --> 00:27:11,396
- You did that during Cops and Robbers?
- You're serious?

777
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:12,764
- Did you?
- It just happened.

778
00:27:12,831 --> 00:27:15,734
It was the first time
a man had done that to me.

779
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:17,369
- You did what?
- So that's why...

780
00:27:17,436 --> 00:27:19,138
- Did you think you were a real cop?
- Yes.

781
00:27:19,204 --> 00:27:20,873
- And another thing--
- I got confused for a second.

782
00:27:20,939 --> 00:27:22,941
- This guy...
- I got too immersed in the game,

783
00:27:23,008 --> 00:27:24,510
and thought you were an actual robber.

784
00:27:28,213 --> 00:27:31,283
Ha-jun is genuinely interested in UFO...
I mean UFC.

785
00:27:31,350 --> 00:27:33,585
- Did you say "UFOC"?
- UFOC?

786
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:35,053
- UFO?
- What was it?

787
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:36,155
UFC.

788
00:27:36,221 --> 00:27:38,490
- He even carries these around.
- Right.

789
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:41,059
Why would you carry those around?

790
00:27:41,126 --> 00:27:42,528
- To catch robbers, of course.
- I heard you're planning to participate.

791
00:27:42,594 --> 00:27:46,165
- The gloves don't even matter.
- To catch robbers.

792
00:27:46,298 --> 00:27:48,167
- He's always shadowboxing.
- That's true.

793
00:27:48,233 --> 00:27:49,201
- For real?
- Yes.

794
00:27:49,268 --> 00:27:50,836
- How?
- Even in the green room?

795
00:27:50,903 --> 00:27:53,071
- Show us how you do it.
- It's not just in the green room.

796
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:54,439
Say we have to do a kiss scene.

797
00:27:54,506 --> 00:27:55,874
Does he kiss like this?

798
00:27:56,141 --> 00:27:58,944
Right before a kissing scene,
I'd see him walk toward me like...

799
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:03,282
- What, seriously?
- Wait.

800
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:05,217
- Seriously.
- Doesn't that break the mood?

801
00:28:05,284 --> 00:28:06,919
- Why did you do that?
- Whenever he does that...

802
00:28:06,985 --> 00:28:08,453
- Were you nervous?
- It's my routine.

803
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,223
- That's what he does before every scene.
- Really?

804
00:28:11,423 --> 00:28:12,691
- For real.
- Do you love doing it that much?

805
00:28:12,991 --> 00:28:14,026
It's just a habit.

806
00:28:14,092 --> 00:28:16,228
How do you do it?
Put these on and show us.

807
00:28:16,295 --> 00:28:18,463
Well, let's say we have

808
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:20,299
- an intimate scene ahead of us.
- Okay.

809
00:28:20,365 --> 00:28:22,100
And we're coordinating the moves, right?

810
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:25,737
"I'll go like this, and then you do this."

811
00:28:25,938 --> 00:28:27,506
"I'll go like this,

812
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:29,841
and then you do this.
Then I counter with..."

813
00:28:30,842 --> 00:28:31,843
"Then I counter with..."

814
00:28:33,045 --> 00:28:34,213
What is this?

815
00:28:34,746 --> 00:28:37,115
"If you twist like that,
then I go in with another punch."

816
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:41,119
I've done a lot of romance scenes
in my life, you know.

817
00:28:43,021 --> 00:28:45,357
- But this...
- He kept jabbing before romantic scenes.

818
00:28:47,759 --> 00:28:50,128
I've never had a male actor do this

819
00:28:50,395 --> 00:28:52,164
before a kissing scene.

820
00:28:52,864 --> 00:28:54,700
- I was just lightening the mood.
- Explain yourself.

821
00:28:54,766 --> 00:28:56,735
- You have to explain yourself.
- Here's the thing.

822
00:28:57,069 --> 00:28:59,104
- I just get shy and embarrassed.
- Oh, you get shy?

823
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:00,906
That's cute.

824
00:29:00,973 --> 00:29:03,408
Can you show me more?
I want to learn boxing, too.

825
00:29:03,542 --> 00:29:05,844
- You want to see more shadowboxing?
- Yes.

826
00:29:05,911 --> 00:29:07,946
- Let's see something cool.
- Should I do it here?

827
00:29:08,013 --> 00:29:08,847
Okay.

828
00:29:08,914 --> 00:29:10,616
Why are you looking at me
while you're practicing?

829
00:29:10,983 --> 00:29:13,018
- Don't look at me when you practice!
- Wait a minute.

830
00:29:13,418 --> 00:29:15,687
- Please don't punch her for real.
- Don't do it.

831
00:29:15,754 --> 00:29:17,522
Calm down!

832
00:29:19,224 --> 00:29:21,627
Oh, he's serious about this!

833
00:29:22,427 --> 00:29:23,428
That's impressive.

834
00:29:25,197 --> 00:29:28,233
Seriously? Do you hate me that much?

835
00:29:33,538 --> 00:29:35,307
That's so cool!

836
00:29:36,041 --> 00:29:37,175
You were punching like this.

837
00:29:37,242 --> 00:29:40,279
How much did you practice
for it to become a habit?

838
00:29:40,379 --> 00:29:42,247
I learned to box a little
when I was young,

839
00:29:42,648 --> 00:29:44,516
and now I do a bit of mixed martial arts.

840
00:29:44,583 --> 00:29:45,684
Like in the UFC?

841
00:29:45,751 --> 00:29:48,820
A little bit of kickboxing,
a little bit of wrestling, and others.

842
00:29:48,887 --> 00:29:50,255
It incorporates different
combat sports techniques.

843
00:29:50,322 --> 00:29:52,958
It's so cool
when a guy is athletic like that.

844
00:29:53,025 --> 00:29:54,693
- That was so cool and fast.
- That was cool.

845
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:55,794
You seem strong.

846
00:29:55,861 --> 00:29:58,830
I heard Ha-jun lied at an audition once.

847
00:29:58,897 --> 00:30:00,098
Why did you do that?

848
00:30:00,432 --> 00:30:02,701
- Oh, that audition?
- You lied once?

849
00:30:03,035 --> 00:30:05,937
It was right after
I was discharged from the military.

850
00:30:06,405 --> 00:30:08,140
I got called back for a final audition.

851
00:30:08,507 --> 00:30:10,575
At the time,
I really wanted to grow out my hair

852
00:30:10,642 --> 00:30:12,477
after the long military service.

853
00:30:12,878 --> 00:30:14,646
I was planning to grow out my hair,

854
00:30:14,713 --> 00:30:16,114
but they asked me
if I could shave my head.

855
00:30:18,183 --> 00:30:19,284
I told them I could.

856
00:30:19,351 --> 00:30:21,186
Then they asked me, "Do you smoke too?"

857
00:30:21,753 --> 00:30:25,223
To be honest,
I absolutely abhorred cigarettes.

858
00:30:26,124 --> 00:30:27,259
- "Abhorred"?
- Yes.

859
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:28,460
- You never smoked?
- I hated it.

860
00:30:28,527 --> 00:30:29,928
- And you hate the smell?
- Yes.

861
00:30:31,530 --> 00:30:32,764
But I told them, "Sure.

862
00:30:33,332 --> 00:30:34,599
I don't smoke right now,

863
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:36,101
- but I did before."
- I see.

864
00:30:36,168 --> 00:30:37,836
I was 24 years old at the time.

865
00:30:37,903 --> 00:30:39,338
Did you get the feeling

866
00:30:39,404 --> 00:30:41,206
- that there would be a smoking scene?
- There would be one.

867
00:30:41,273 --> 00:30:42,741
- Yes.
- Exactly.

868
00:30:42,808 --> 00:30:44,843
Then they asked me if I could drive.
I didn't even have a license.

869
00:30:45,544 --> 00:30:47,312
- Hold on. This is...
- Wait a minute.

870
00:30:47,379 --> 00:30:48,580
This could've been really dangerous.

871
00:30:48,647 --> 00:30:50,449
- What were you thinking?
- What did you say?

872
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:52,584
I told them I could drive.

873
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:56,321
Well, I assumed I wouldn't get the role.

874
00:30:56,388 --> 00:30:58,023
- But you got it?
- Really?

875
00:30:58,090 --> 00:31:00,959
I played the younger version
of Um Tae-goo's character

876
00:31:01,026 --> 00:31:03,028
who smokes and drives at the same time.

877
00:31:03,929 --> 00:31:05,764
How did you manage that?

878
00:31:05,831 --> 00:31:08,133
- You can't drive, and you hate smoking.
- Exactly.

879
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,968
- Yes, that was a tough one.
- Both were in one scene.

880
00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:11,436
I lied at the audition

881
00:31:11,770 --> 00:31:13,205
thinking I wouldn't get it,

882
00:31:13,605 --> 00:31:14,973
- but as it turned out...
- You got it.

883
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,074
- Yes.
- Oh my.

884
00:31:16,141 --> 00:31:17,209
What did you do?

885
00:31:17,275 --> 00:31:19,144
I immediately enrolled
in a driving school.

886
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:21,480
- That was the right thing to do.
- Goodness.

887
00:31:21,613 --> 00:31:24,116
I managed to get a driving license.

888
00:31:24,182 --> 00:31:25,217
What about smoking?

889
00:31:25,283 --> 00:31:29,354
A friend I was practicing with
took me to the rooftop

890
00:31:29,421 --> 00:31:31,723
- and taught me how to smoke.
- He helped you?

891
00:31:32,457 --> 00:31:34,593
I nearly broke down crying that day.

892
00:31:34,659 --> 00:31:36,495
- You were fighting against yourself.
- Yes.

893
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:40,966
I told myself that
this would've happened sooner or later,

894
00:31:41,233 --> 00:31:44,536
- especially since I liked noir films too.
- Right.

895
00:31:44,603 --> 00:31:47,139
So I would've had to smoke
sooner or later.

896
00:31:47,305 --> 00:31:49,674
But I didn't think it'd be so soon.

897
00:31:49,741 --> 00:31:52,344
- To top it off, the day of the shooting
- That must've been hard.

898
00:31:52,411 --> 00:31:53,545
was my birthday.

899
00:31:54,679 --> 00:31:56,648
So I was smoking on my birthday

900
00:31:56,715 --> 00:31:58,316
- Goodness.
- with my hair shaved...

901
00:31:58,383 --> 00:31:59,751
- All for the role.
- Doing what you abhorred.

902
00:31:59,818 --> 00:32:02,821
But all of that made you
who you are today!

903
00:32:03,321 --> 00:32:06,391
- That's true.
- I'm sure that was a valuable experience.

904
00:32:06,458 --> 00:32:08,527
I started working
with my current agency back then.

905
00:32:09,795 --> 00:32:10,896
Where's the owner?

906
00:32:10,962 --> 00:32:12,764
- Welcome.
- Yes, welcome.

907
00:32:12,831 --> 00:32:14,866
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

908
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:17,135
- Are you kidding me?
- Sorry?

909
00:32:17,702 --> 00:32:18,837
What's wrong?

910
00:32:18,904 --> 00:32:21,673
Look, I ordered this yesterday.

911
00:32:21,740 --> 00:32:23,175
- Yesterday?
- Yes,

912
00:32:23,241 --> 00:32:24,810
- but I was too busy to come until now.
- Okay.

913
00:32:25,010 --> 00:32:27,012
The thing is, there was hair in it.

914
00:32:27,446 --> 00:32:29,548
- There was hair in the food?
- That makes no sense.

915
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:30,749
- I want a refund.
- It can't be possible.

916
00:32:30,816 --> 00:32:31,817
Where?

917
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:33,685
Can't you see it right there?

918
00:32:33,752 --> 00:32:35,153
I'm being completely serious.

919
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:36,221
Oh, come on.

920
00:32:36,288 --> 00:32:38,156
- I see you've finished it off anyway.
- You ate it all.

921
00:32:38,223 --> 00:32:40,091
I was too busy to come yesterday.

922
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:41,860
Hold on. This can't be our hair.

923
00:32:41,927 --> 00:32:43,428
We both have longer hair.

924
00:32:43,495 --> 00:32:45,197
- Yes, and I have curls.
- See?

925
00:32:45,263 --> 00:32:47,532
- This hair is too straight to be ours.
- Look at this bastard.

926
00:32:47,599 --> 00:32:50,335
- This isn't right.
- Don't try to trick us, man.

927
00:32:50,402 --> 00:32:52,137
- Let him have it, Ha-jun.
- This is ridiculous.

928
00:32:52,204 --> 00:32:53,371
First of all,

929
00:32:53,438 --> 00:32:55,106
RUNNING A SIMULATION
the length is completely wrong.

930
00:32:55,173 --> 00:32:57,309
It's obviously your hair.

931
00:32:57,375 --> 00:32:58,677
Help us out here.

932
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:00,011
- He's being too rude.
- What?

933
00:33:00,078 --> 00:33:01,746
- What?
- You're being impossible, mister.

934
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:04,349
I see you actually ate
all of the fried chicken.

935
00:33:04,416 --> 00:33:05,917
- All but three small pieces.
- Listen.

936
00:33:05,984 --> 00:33:09,087
You ate too much of it to demand a refund.

937
00:33:09,154 --> 00:33:10,555
But there was a hair in it!

938
00:33:10,622 --> 00:33:12,858
- Why did you keep doing this anyway?
- No, don't...

939
00:33:12,924 --> 00:33:14,459
- I'm just saying...
- Are you picking a fight with me?

940
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:16,361
Calm down, Min-young!

941
00:33:16,428 --> 00:33:17,696
- What's this?
- She's here.

942
00:33:17,762 --> 00:33:20,432
- Is this your hair, lady?
- Let it go, Min-young.

943
00:33:20,599 --> 00:33:22,300
How dare you accuse us like that?

944
00:33:22,434 --> 00:33:23,935
You think I'm lying?

945
00:33:24,002 --> 00:33:25,570
You want me to leave a horrible review?

946
00:33:26,271 --> 00:33:27,305
- Is that what you want?
- Hey.

947
00:33:27,372 --> 00:33:29,107
- Excuse me.
- What?

948
00:33:29,174 --> 00:33:31,710
Can I run a DNA test on this hair?

949
00:33:31,943 --> 00:33:32,911
A DNA...

950
00:33:35,380 --> 00:33:36,648
You're all in on it, aren't you?

951
00:33:36,715 --> 00:33:38,650
You're making me out to be the bad guy!

952
00:33:38,717 --> 00:33:40,051
Do you think I'm lying?

953
00:33:40,118 --> 00:33:42,454
- No, we just...
- Then go ahead and pull out a hair.

954
00:33:42,721 --> 00:33:43,788
- I'm doing it.
- Okay.

955
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:45,156
Should I get the gray one?

956
00:33:45,223 --> 00:33:47,092
- I have gray hair?
- You do.

957
00:33:47,158 --> 00:33:48,894
Wait, no need to do it like that.

958
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,862
See? This is easier.

959
00:33:50,929 --> 00:33:52,063
It's a nice sample.

960
00:33:52,130 --> 00:33:53,265
Take them all.

961
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:54,566
- Then I'll--
- You actually tore out my hair.

962
00:33:54,966 --> 00:33:57,035
- We'll get them tested.
- I grabbed a fistful.

963
00:33:57,102 --> 00:33:59,404
If they match the hair in the box,

964
00:33:59,471 --> 00:34:02,407
you might find yourself
in a difficult position.

965
00:34:02,974 --> 00:34:05,443
- She doesn't mess around, you know.
- That's right.

966
00:34:05,610 --> 00:34:07,379
Why do you keep doing that anyway, man?

967
00:34:07,646 --> 00:34:08,780
Are you a strong fighter?

968
00:34:09,214 --> 00:34:10,515
I wouldn't say I'm bad at fighting.

969
00:34:10,849 --> 00:34:12,751
It's dangerous, Min-young. Come here.

970
00:34:12,817 --> 00:34:14,185
It's okay.

971
00:34:17,622 --> 00:34:19,324
Hold on.

972
00:34:19,391 --> 00:34:21,726
Wait a minute.

973
00:34:21,793 --> 00:34:24,529
This is just too...

974
00:34:24,696 --> 00:34:26,431
- This is too sad.
- Wait.

975
00:34:26,698 --> 00:34:28,199
It's just...

976
00:34:28,266 --> 00:34:29,801
Your head is so big.

977
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:32,537
I mean, it's just so...

978
00:34:32,604 --> 00:34:35,307
I came to get my money back,
not get insulted about my head size.

979
00:34:35,373 --> 00:34:37,075
This is incredible.

980
00:34:37,142 --> 00:34:39,411
What's incredible is that
I found a hair in your chicken!

981
00:34:39,477 --> 00:34:41,313
Give me my money back

982
00:34:41,379 --> 00:34:42,747
if you don't want a horrible review.

983
00:34:42,814 --> 00:34:44,449
Excuse me. Could you wipe your drool?

984
00:34:44,516 --> 00:34:47,118
- You should wipe it.
